      <title>[Letter] 1813 March 22 [to] Colonel Sevier / John Sevier</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This document is a letter dated March 22, 1813 to Colonel Sevier, written by his father, former Governor of Tennessee, John Sevier. Sevier discusses various topics in the letter, including the War of 1812, a lawsuit against Polk, and the condition of his son's mare.</abstract>
